{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772379234,"nonce":"q05Pqx/Sky+Yp1T2r4OzBRcYNSI=","title":"Generate identicons for users and borrowers","message":"Redux currently has a hardcoded placeholder avatar in the user menu. v1 generated identicons via RubyIdenticon seeded from name+email/department.\n\nRedux should generate identicons rather than using a static placeholder. This defeats the purpose of having avatars at all.\n\n## Context\n\n- v1 used RubyIdenticon gem, stored Base64 in avatar_data column\n- Redux dropped avatar_data but kept a hardcoded placeholder PNG in _user_menu.html.erb\n- During d1 migration, v1 avatar_data will be dropped (not migrated)\n- Redux needs its own identicon generation\n\n## Scope\n\n- Pick an identicon approach (RubyIdenticon gem, or CSS/JS based, or server-generated SVG)\n- Generate for users and borrowers based on name/email\n- Replace hardcoded placeholder in user menu\n- Show in borrower views where appropriate","files":null}]}